	    	// Also it provides a way to ensure that each request has been correctly identified and authenticated.  No other user's data is accessible or manipulated beyond the scope of this session id which ensures privacy & integrity on every transaction between two users in any platform ie web, mobile apps etc..   due JWT tokens are used as authentication token for all our requests but we can use these sessions to track and authorize activities.
    		// It's important security measure against unauthorized access/modification of the user data stored within a request by an authorized session ID only, it ensures privacy & integrity on every transaction between two users in any platform ie web application context (like Spring Web MVC).   Due to JWT tokens are used as authentication token for all our requests but we can use these sessions/cookies or jwts 
    		// To manage user logins, and access controls across different devices. This is a secure way of managing users in real-time environments (such web applications) when sensitive information should be kept private ie only authentication tokens are stored on the client side for better security while accessing server data using these session/cookies or jwts from anywhere inside our app without exposing actual user's login credentials.
    		// It helps to maintain confidentiality and integrity of personal identifiable Information (PII) in real-time applications ie when access token is only valid for a specific period, users should be able log out after the expiry date or they can refresh their tokens on another request without having them logged back into our app.
    		// It's important security measure against unauthorized user data modification due to authentication-related identifiers stored within requests and needs authorization for operations beyond that scope in any platform ie web, mobile apps etc..   Due to JWT tokens are used as auth token from the server side but we can use these sessions/cookies or jwts 
    		// To keep sensitive information private like passwords. In a real-time environment such data should be encrypted for security and privacy reasons ie when access is given only through valid session id's, users are not exposed to the actual user login credentials due JWT tokens from server side as they stay secure in their client browser until expiry/expiration of token.
